snippet.textDisplay: I was ready to criticize this interview before I watched and listened to it. I almost hate that every time people die, TV anchors invade their "mournfulness" and frequently ask the stupidest questions (which the one obliged us and did here, "Are you angry?") Why is that TV material? Because it makes money!! They may truly care, I don't deny that. Just like I do, for this guy and his family. But they always ask stupid questions (Can we say that enough?) so they can have one of their TV moments go viral. I honestly don't understand why family of the deceased agree to interviews. This also seems weird to me. I'm glad to know about this woman, Christine, though. And I can see why he is scared. Hope they have a lot of support. There is no complete healing to a death so close, though. Kids can't ever get Mommy back. Then I think of all the kids in the world who have absent or not parents. It's rough. Joining Big Brother, Big Sister or as after school program volunteers are the only things we can do! Make a difference in one life, if possible.
